Existing Classifications. Despite the breadth of current taxonomies,
existing classifications are primarily feature-based rather than
semantics-based. A critical limitation identified by Belchior et al.
(2021) is that while technical and functional layers are addressed, "few
solutions focus on the semantic layer". Semantic
interoperability---ensuring the "meaning embedded in the information" is
correctly understood by consuming systems---remains an "ongoing
